   The Role

   The role holder will be responsible for the Retail portfolio in arrears, minimising bad debts through stringent credit control and ensuring adequate provisioning for a growing portfolio. The role holder will work within and contribute to a strong controlled environment, incorporating financial controls and procedures, legislation and risk management.

   Key Responsibilities

     * Responsible for the collection and the maintenance of account receivables: contact customers, follow up on payments and engage late payers to maximise collection efficiency.
     * Manage inbound and outbound telephone calls while processing the daily direct debit unpaid file
     * Manage the 0 - 90 days in arrears queue together with Default / Legal (90+ days in arrears) cases
     * Process Visa Debit/ Laser Card payments and the represented direct debits
     * Upload the next day's Direct Debit unpaid file
     * Process the collections administration relating to Contra settlements, invalid bank accounts, address changes and bank account changes
     * To provide cover as needed for the team

   Key Person Requirements

     * 2 + years' experience in negotiating with customers and identifying restructuring situations
     * Ability to deal with customers confidently and in a professional manner
     * Awareness of the Code of Conduct, Hire Purchase Terms and Conditions, Section 54 and Termination process
     * Excellent verbal and written communication skills with the ability to articulate and document the rationale for decisions, an ability to manage difficult conversations and problem solving capabilities
     * Knowledge of managing customers, particularly those with deteriorating financial positions
     * Ability to work within a small team and collaboratively with colleagues
     * Good level of numeracy and strong Microsoft suite skills

   This is an MCC impacted role. Applicants must have a relevant qualification (APA Loans or QFA) with their CPD requirements up to date.

   Terms &amp; Conditions

   This is a full time temporary position. A competitive remuneration package commensurate with experience and qualification level will be offered to the successful candidate
